            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1349316755,
            "creation_date": 1349316755,
            "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p>[is] there was a built in method or functionality where I could detect if a booleans value had changed in the function?<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>You can do it by encapsulating access to your <code>boolean<\/code> variables using setters:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private boolean test1 = true;\nprivate boolean test2 = true;\n\nprivate void setTest1(boolean newTest1) {\n    if (newTest1 != test1) {\n        // Do something\n    }\n}\n\nprivate void setTest2(boolean newTest2) {\n    if (newTest2 != test2) {\n        // Do something\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Replace all assignments of these variables with calls of <code>setTest1<\/code> and <code>setTest2<\/code> to get reliable detection of changes in <code>test1<\/code> and <code>test2<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 12719428,
            "question_id": 12719390
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/48cfe5767eacc4cc2c8fbf1b116b5dea?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1798723,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1637543,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1637543/romedius",
                "reputation": 775,
                "display_name": "romedius",
                "accept_rate": 88
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1349316885,
            "creation_date": 1349316885,
            "body": "<p>1) make the booleans private<br>\n2) access them via getters and setters<br>\n3) in the setter: 'if (this.val!=newVal) notify()'<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 12719442,
            "question_id": 12719390
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/041051373ade01fb8e44342f33716481?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
